com.yantra.yfc.rcp

Class YRCLinkBindingData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCLinkBindingData

  • public class YRCLinkBindingData
extends java.lang.Object
    Instances of this class provide binding, behavioral and name information about Link controls.
    Usage: //Create a binding object that has to be associated with a control. YRCLinkBindingData linkBindingData = new YRCLinkBindingData(); //Set the name of the control. The control name should be unique. linkBindingData.setName("linkDetails"); // Set the action id whose shortcut should be displayed along with the // text on the link. linkBindingData.setActionId("some.action.id.associated.with.the.link"); //Set the source binding for the link. The text from the biding is used //to set the text on the control. linkBindingData.setSourceBinding("/Order/@Description"); //Finally set the binding data on the control. The key used is: YRCConstants.YRC_LINK_BINDING_DEFINATION linkControl.setData(YRCConstants.YRC_LINK_BINDING_DEFINATION, linkBindingData);

      • setDynamic

        public void setDynamic(boolean isDynamic)
        Boolean value to indicate that the link is populated dynamically. When this boolean is set, during the setModel(String, Element) from the behavior of the screen , the behavior is called internally to get the text to be populated on the control. The method: evaluateDynamicBinding(String, Element) is called in the screen's behavior.
        Parameters:
        isDynamic - true if the binding needs to be dynamic.
        See Also:
